/u0/chip/habitat/doc/system:
	This directory contains most of the original Habitat system design
documents.  Here you will find:

DOC		- this file
adventures.itr	- doc #13 first pass at defining activities and things to do
animation.itr	- doc #18 original spec for avatar animation cels
coming.itr	- doc #27 discussion of realms and regions for beta world
coord.itr	- doc #4 coordinate systems and topology
databases.itr	- doc #19 host database requirements
death.itr	- doc #37 how avatar death works
definition.itr	- dictionary definition of "microcosm"
drop.itr	- document on minor design problem
enddef.itr	- doc #28 early definition of release system
extensions.itr	- doc #25 possible extensions to Habitat
features.itr	- system components description (very early)
firstMagic.itr	- doc #30 spec for preliminary magic stuff
funativity.itr	- doc #22 more on stuff to do in Habitat
gateway.itr	- doc #24 commentary on realm-oriented extensions
graphics.itr	- doc #15 spec for C64 graphics implementation
homearch.itr	- doc #12 spec for C64 general system architecture
hostarch.itr	- doc #8 spec for host general system architecture
iface.itr	- doc #6 spec for user interface
intomic.itr	- doc #10 comments on 3rd party software inside Habitat
looi.itr	- doc #2 spec for LOOI
machiavelli.itr	- doc #24 design for Machiavelli sub-game
mail.itr	- doc #33 spec for Habitat mail
maps.itr	- doc #17 early guidelines for world layout
memload.itr	- doc #40 analysis of C64 memory usage
microcosm.itr	- doc #1 original proposal
minobs.itr	- doc #16 minimal object set spec
noodl.itr	- doc #3 spec for NOODL
noodl.y		- file included in NOODL spec
objectform.itr	- doc #47b object test checklist
obman.tbl	- doc #20 exhaustive object manual
oracle.itr	- doc #31 oracle capabilities design
portmic.itr	- doc #9 considerations about alternative hosts
protocols.tbl	- doc #14 object message protocol description
rantads.itr	- doc #36 policy on advertizing in the Rant
reno.itr	- doc #29 proposal for RENO
scenarios.itr	- doc #23 more things to do in Habitat
shortwh.itr	- doc #5 sample Habitat interaction writeup (promo doc)
